claim: Flublok contains 3x the hemagglutinin (HA) antigen content of standard-dose flu vaccines, which has been linked to greater immunogenicity vs standard-dose flu vaccines.
explanation: A table summarizing contraindications and precautions for influenza vaccines available in 2022–23, categorized by vaccine type (egg-based IIVs and LAIV4, ccIIV4, RIV4) in the context of previous severe allergic reactions (e.g., anaphylaxis). does not support the claim – the table only addresses allergic reaction contraindications and precautions for different vaccine types and does not present any data on hemagglutinin antigen content or immunogenicity. Note: The image is clear but focuses exclusively on safety/contraindication information, with no mention of antigen dose or immunogenicity.
